blog.title: If You’re Looking For Formality Go Away
blog.description: reviews for new (and things I need to catch up on) movies, tv, and music

body:
Good Omens 👼🏼😈

OOOO SO GOOD, we love an angel/demon complex… here’s everything in categories so you don’t get confused. Warning: *spoilers* and *unprofessional review*

Good stuff:

- softboi!Aziraphale

- nanny!Crowley

- i’ve seen people complain about all of David’s wigs but honestly, he’s beautiful in all of them so shhh (I’m waiting for someone to make a post of just his outfits)

- all the eras represented, I’m in love

- the baby swap

- The Almighty narrator

- the montage of Aziraphale and Crowley over the earth’s lifetime

- Crowley making fun of Azirphale healing the bike

- honestly all of Crowley and Aziraphale made me happy

- CROWLEY FREAKING OUT WHEN HE THOUGHT AZIRAPHALE WAS DEAD

- the book shop

- witches and prophecies

- David Tennant

- Antony “just a j” Crowley ^ “you don’t like it?” “I didn’t say that”

- oof, we’re in for a slow burn

- QUEEN MUSIC, all day baby Also *cough* somebody to love *cough* subtle *cough*

- crepes

- the ritz

- “I made Michael miracle me a towel”


Bad stuff:

- so many unresolved things??? Like is Satan… dead? Is the witch squad completely disbanded? Are Aziraphale and Crowley married yet???

- WE GOT BENEDICT FREAKIN CUMBERBATCH FOR LIKE AT TOPS 20 seconds??

- rushed witch and witch hunter relationship? Am I the only one who wanted this to be a like… not rushed?

- they burned Agnes’ second book, like I get it ~ character development ~ but still, she was a badass witch goddess and they were like “eh let’s just ignore her wishes”

- they never told us what happened to the third kid? Or even Warlock, like what was up with that guy, or his name…

- 6 episodes??? Who’s idea was this (I need more nooooow) ps this is dangerous for binge watchers like me

- the other angels and demons were super lame and unthreatening lol (that made it funny though so not that bad)


Human stuff (other):

- this needed to be a category lol

- it was extremely reminiscent of supernatural

- do seances allow angels to come into your body? Is that what that was?

- i think it’s kinda funny that the kids were all suddenly perfectly normal after literally coming into contact with the four horseman of the apocalypse and somehow defeating them? And after their best friend(/leader?) tortured them?? But I mean, 11 year olds, am I right

- why didn’t Crowley take his car? Was he afraid of scratching it? Lol

- what was the significance of the new set of books tho

- angels and demons against all of humanity sounds fun

- I kinda wanted them to both actually be immune to hellfire and holy water, but you know I get how that could make it hard to seem like they’re ever in trouble

- someone tell me rn if there will be another season plz

- more refined!Aziraphale now plz

- finally, there are no good angel/demon emojis, please fix this Apple

summary: David Tennant Can’t Stop Saving the World
title: David Tennant Can’t Stop Saving the World
excerpt: The Scottish actor breaks down his new demonic role on 'Good Omens' and his historic 'Doctor Who' run.
description:
Interviewer: This is a genre-driven, really stylized, lots of plot going on, kind of story. But at the heart, as you said, it’s a buddy movie; it’s about two people who enjoy each other’s company and wanting to spend a bit more time with each other.

DT: It’s a real collision of the cosmic and the domestic. At heart, it’s about two very human supernatural beings, actually, who are almost more human than everyone else around them.

Interviewer: I suppose you could say they’re accustomed to a human way of life now.

DT: They’ve definitely gone native, yeah. They have no interest in the end of the world. They enjoy the… texture of the mortal world, they enjoy glasses of wine and dinners and nice restaurants. They don’t need them, of course, but they appreciate the joy of it, which their respective head offices don’t understand at all.

Interviewer: I like how Crowley is causing definite mayhem, but his other demons don’t seem to understand quite how much taking down London’s cell phone towers will actually cause as much chaos as it would. They want “traditional” evil.

DT: That’s the other thing: it works as a workplace comedy as well, that the bosses are idiots and the workers are being sent down blind alleys by them all the time. I think there’s lots of relatable stuff even though it’s a story about the supernatural.

Interviewer: One particularly fun episode has you and Michael Sheen throughout the ages, pretty much. And then it takes up half the episode and then the opening credits come in-

DT: Can I tell you? That’s one of my favorite things. I keep calling it the longest cold open in television history, and I don’t know if that's—

Interviewer: Ooh! That’s not true!

DT: It’s not true? What beats us?

Interviewer: Have you heard of The OA on Netflix? Their opening sequence happens at the end of the first episode, an hour in.

DT: Oh my God. Not even close! Ah! Still, we had a stab at it. 28 minutes, I believe. Darn! Beat by The OA. Oh well.

Interviewer: I have to ask: were those contacts or was it CGI for your eyes? They looked excruciating.

DT: I wear contact lenses anyway, so I had an advantage. And they put my prescription in. So there are two types of them, the ones that just fit over the color part of your eye, and then for those particularly demonic moments, the ones that fit the whole eye. I’m glad, though, that they look more extreme than they felt.
